# Macrotide — operator config. Copy to `.env.local` and fill what you need.
# `.env.local` is gitignored; commit only this template.

# ─── App URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used for OpenRouter referer + WebAuthn passkey origin in production.
# In dev, http://localhost:3000 is always trusted.
PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# ─── Auth (better-auth + passkey) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Auth is REQUIRED by default — the dashboard bounces to /login until
# a passkey is registered. Secure-by-default: misconfiguring (e.g. exposing
# the port) fails closed, not open. See SECURITY.md for the threat model.
#
# Opt out ONLY for local dev when you're the sole user on loopback:
# AUTH_DISABLED=1

# Generate with `openssl rand -base64 32`. Required when auth is enabled.
# The code has a "macrotide-dev-secret-change-me" fallback so `npm run dev`
# works without setup, but you MUST set this in any real deployment.
# AUTH_SECRET=

# Optional — Relying Party config. Defaults: rpName="Macrotide", rpID inferred
# from PUBLIC_APP_URL host. Override only if you understand WebAuthn rpID rules.
# AUTH_RP_NAME=Macrotide
# AUTH_RP_ID=macrotide.example.com

# ─── AI provider (OpenRouter) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Macrotide routes all chat through OpenRouter (one key, every major model).
# Sign up at https://openrouter.ai to get a key; pricing is per-token credit.
#
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
#
# Model chain (comma-separated, first is primary, rest are fallbacks).
# Default: `openrouter/free,openrouter/auto` — try free models first, fall
# back to paid `auto` only if every free model is unavailable. Override with
# any model id from openrouter.ai/models (e.g. `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5`).
# AI_MODELS=openrouter/free,openrouter/auto

# ─── AI provider (demo-side) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# Demo chat is routed through a separate key so demo usage can never burn
# your owner key's quota. Capped at 10 turns per demo session.
#
# Easiest setup: leave DEMO_OPENROUTER_API_KEY unset — demo falls back to
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY, and the default `openrouter/free` (no paid fallback)
# picks zero-cost models per request. Demo errors cleanly if free is
# unavailable rather than silently billing.
#
# For stricter isolation, create a second OpenRouter key and set:
# DEMO_OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
# DEMO_AI_MODELS=openrouter/free                          # default; no fallback
# DEMO_AI_MODELS=meta-llama/llama-3.3-70b-instruct:free   # pin a specific one

# ─── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Path to the SQLite file. Default: data/app.db (auto-created).
# DB_PATH=data/app.db

# ─── Thai SEC Open API (Thai mutual fund NAVs) ─────────────────────────────
# Powers the `thfund:` provider. Without a key, holdings tagged
# `thfund:...` render as "—".
#
# Portal: https://secopendata.sec.or.th/sec-open-apis
# Sign in, create one Subscription, copy either Primary or Secondary key
# below. Both keys are identical in capability — the pair exists so you
# can rotate without downtime (swap app to Secondary, regenerate Primary,
# swap back). A single subscription covers all 6 product groups (bond,
# fund, digital-asset, LicenseCheck, onereport, pvd).
#
# Header: Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key (Azure APIM).
# Rate limit: 5,000 calls / 300 s. HTTP 421 = over-limit; respect Retry-After.
# Refresh windows: 09:30 + 17:30 Bangkok time.
#
# The portal warns explicitly: NEVER publish your Subscription Key on
# GitHub, websites, or any public file. .env.local is gitignored — keep
# the key there, never in the committed .env.example.
# SEC_API_KEY=
